## crates/ctx-cage/src/proxy.rs

Host-side HTTP-over-UNIX-socket-to-TLS proxy: the sole egress point for an offline cage. The in-cage relay forwards `127.0.0.1:8080` to a UNIX socket bind-mounted at `/run/ctx/api.sock`; this file accepts those connections, rewrites the request head, dials the upstream API over TLS, and pumps bytes in both directions.

Two auth postures, selected by `ProxyConfig.api_key`: `Some(key)` strips any client-supplied `x-api-key`/`Authorization` header and injects the real key host-side (cage never sees it); `None` passes the client's own `Authorization` through untouched (subscription-OAuth posture). `is_owned_header` encodes exactly which headers the proxy takes over ‚Äî `Host` and `Connection` always, `x-api-key`/`Authorization` only when injecting ‚Äî and `rewrite_head` is a pure function over head text built from that predicate, easy to unit-test without sockets.

TLS/process-spawning is quarantined behind the `Upstream` trait; the real impl (`SocatUpstream`) shells out to `socat -t 86400 - OPENSSL:<host>:443,verify=1,...` rather than linking a TLS crate ‚Äî the long timeout (`86400`s) is a deliberate half-close workaround referenced as "the ADR-028 lesson." No TLS library is used directly in this crate; swapping upstream behavior means implementing `Upstream`, not editing this file's socket code.

`read_head` scans for `\r\n\r\n`, capping at `MAX_HEAD` (64 KiB) and erroring (`CageError::Protocol`) on EOF-before-terminator or oversize ‚Äî never panics on malformed input, but leftover body bytes already read past the head are captured and forwarded verbatim (not re-parsed as HTTP framing ‚Äî no chunked/length awareness anywhere in this file).

`serve_conn<U: Upstream>(client, cfg, upstream) -> Result<(), CageError>` handles one connection: reads head, rewrites it, dials, writes rewritten head + leftover bytes upstream, then pumps client‚Üíupstream on a spawned thread while pumping upstream‚Üíclient on the calling thread; shuts down and joins on completion. `serve<U: Upstream + 'static>(listener, cfg: &Arc<ProxyConfig>, upstream: &Arc<U>, stop: &AtomicBool) -> Result<(), CageError>` is a nonblocking accept loop, one thread per connection, polling `stop` every `ACCEPT_IDLE` (20ms) for shutdown. `pump` is best-effort ‚Äî read/write errors silently end the connection, never propagated.